<subSubSection id="309AC4AC2D561E1178B789ED30498FBD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D068EA439D31E707CDC667878699CF3C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05424307738B1364A8EC0687B2845693" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
No original material was found in GRM and in the other surveyed herbaria. Also A. P. V. 
<normalizedToken id="80D2D7B0A996FAB9574B6100BD5A4242" originalValue="Mutel’s">Mutel's</normalizedToken>
Herbarium was checked because he used to include Villars specimens in his own herbarium (M. Lefebvre, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48B519F74668F261EE5F136D6340585D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The neotype designated here matches the protologue and corresponds to the current application of the name, which is accepted by both 
<bibRefCitation id="AC94BF676F3F1E06113062E3CDECFABF" author="Kerguelen, M" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Kerguelen, M, 1993. Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." title="Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." year="1993">
<normalizedToken id="55A82BEBA6CE2F0388BFB3A166B73E0B" originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="DE40D10747E5D7F0BCBED027D549FC24" author="Tison, J-M" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B37" refString="Tison, J-M, de Foucault, B, 2014. Flora Gallica. Flore de France. Biotope Editons, Meze." title="Flora Gallica. Flore de France. Biotope Editons, Meze." year="2014">Tison and de Foucault (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is characterized by having 1 cm long basal leaves, very short, 1-5 cm long single-flowered scapes and epicalyx scales lanceolate with a linear mucro. Concerning the shape of calyx teeth, it is very similar to the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="CD94BBE59756EDC4BEC12A1DEECCD26B" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. inodorus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="inodorus">
<emphasis id="EF0E3F079C3FDDD328E310A78BEE48DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. inodorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Gaertn., which in turn is currently included within the variability of 
<taxonomicName id="3A67FDA772549B4A902BD03DA206D76F" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. sylvestris" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="90F3E8F7EB0E238A101CCF672CAD8997" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0E1B91C886649EE21EEDA10BFEECE437" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" author="Domina, G" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1096 - 1100" refId="B15" refString="Domina, G, Astuti, G, Barone, G, Gargano, D, Minuto, L, Varaldo, L, Peruzzi, L, 2021. Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae). Taxon 70 (5): 1096 - 1100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" title="Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" volume="70" year="2021">Domina et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Further research is needed to clarify the relationships between these two taxa.
</paragraph>
